data.benefitDescription: The rider provides a guaranteed annual lifetime withdrawal benefit and allows the Owner to add a portion of earnings to the otherwise permissible withdrawals. The For Life Guarantee becomes effective on the Contract Anniversary immediately following the Owner (or oldest Owner) attaining age 59 1/2.
data.benefitBaseGeneral: The initial Guaranteed Withdrawal Base (GWB) is equal to the initial purchase payment. On each Contract Anniversary after issue, if the Contract Value is greater than the GWB, the GWB will be automatically reset to the Contract Value on that Contract Anniversary. A 5% for single life and 5% for joint life will apply to the benefit base in years no withdrawals are taken, if greater than the stepped up value. Step-Up also allows for a potential increase in the GAWA percentage in the event that the Step-Up occurs after the first withdrawal. Whether there will be any such increase in the GAWA percentage will depend on a value called the Benefit Determination Baseline (BDB). The initial BDB equals the initial premium, net of applicable premium taxes. Upon Step-Up, if the GWB is greater than the BDB and an age band is crossed, the GAWA percentage will be re-determined based on the attained age of the Owner. Benefit also provides Earnings-Sensitive Adjustment, which is an amount that can be withdrawn each Contract Year when there are benefit earnings, in addition to GAWA while keeping the rider guarantees fully in effect. The adjustment is equal to the lesser of (1) 40% of benefit earnings, 2) 2/3 of the greater of remaining (a) GAWA (b) RMD. If there are no earnings in the benefit, no earnings sensitive adjustment will be applied.
data.benefitBaseNoWithdrawal: A bonus of 5% for single life and 5% for joint life of the Bonus Base will be added to the GWB at the end of each Contract Year within the Bonus Period if no withdrawals have been taken during that Contract Year. The Bonus Base at issue is equal to the GWB. It increases dollar for dollar with subsequent net premiums. If withdrawals in a Contract Year exceed the GAWA plus ESA, the Bonus Base is reset to the lesser of the GWB after the withdrawal and the Bonus Base before the withdrawal. If withdrawals in a contract year do not exceed the GAWA plus ESA no adjustment is made to the bonus base. When the GWB increases on a Step-Up, the Bonus Base is set to the greater of the GWB after, and the Bonus Base before, the Step-Up. The bonus period begins on the effective date of the benefit and is reset at the time of a step-up of the bonus base if the step-up occurs on or before the contract anniversary immediately following the owners ( or older joint owners) 80th Birthday. The Bonus Period ends on the earliest of (1) the 10th Contract Anniversary after rider issue or most recent step up or (3) contract value reduced to zero. It is possible for the Bonus Period to expire and then re-start.
data.benefitBaseEnhanceStep: If no withdrawals are taken before the later of: (1) the Contract Anniversary on or immediately following the 70th birthday or (2) the 12th Contract Anniversary, the GWB will be reset on that date to the greater of the GWB Adjustment or the current GWB. The GWB Adjustment is equal to (1) the 105% of net premiums received in the first Contract Year, plus (3) net premiums received after the first Contract Year.
data.withdrawalNotes: Automatic step-ups after first withdrawal may increase the GAWA percentage.
data.chargeNotes: Charges may increase subject to maximum on each 5th contract anniversary and the owner may elect to opt out of the current and future charges increases.
data.feeOption: Upon step-up on or after 2nd contract anniversary, charge may be increased.

data.availWhenAdded: At contract issue or at any subsequent contract anniversary.
data.change: Once elected may not be changed.
data.effectChangeOwnership: Change in ownership will result in termination of rider except under certain conditions.
data.gmwbCancellation: Once elected may not be cancelled.
data.gmwbTermination: Benefit will automatically terminate upon earliest of - 1) annuitization, 2) surrender, 3) death, or 4) benefit base reduced to zero.
data.subsequentPremium: Subsequent purchase payments increase the GWB dollar for dollar and increase the GAWA by the net premium times the GAWA percent.
data.partialWithdrawals: Withdrawals up to the GAWA or Stretch RMD in the current contact year reduce the GWB by dollar for dollar. Withdrawals in excess of the GAWA or Stretch RMD reduce the GWB and GAWA by the same proportion that the excess withdrawal reduces the Contract Value.
data.reqdMinDistributions: RMD withdrawals in excess of the GAWA or Stretch RMD are not considered to be excess withdrawals.
data.benefitDescription: The Guaranteed Withdrawal Base (GWB) is equal to the initial premium net of any premium taxes if elected at issue. The GWB is equal to the Contract Value if the rider is elected on contract anniversary. At any point in time, the GWB is the remaining amount guaranteed to be paid under the rider benefit.
data.benefitBaseGeneral: The Guaranteed Withdrawal Base (GWB) is equal to the initial premium net of any premium taxes if the rider is added on the contract date. Thereafter, GWB is equal to the Contract Value less recapture charge on any contract enhancement if the rider is added after the contract issue date. At any point in time, the GWB is the remaining amount guaranteed to be paid under the rider benefit.
data.benefitBaseWithdrawal: Owner may withdraw the greater of the GAWA or Stretch RMD, as applicable, all at once or throughout the contract year. Withdrawing less than the greater of the GAWA or Stretch RMD, as applicable, in a contract year does not entitle owner to withdraw more than the greater of the GAWA or Stretch RMD, as applicable, in the next contract year. The amount owner may withdraw each contract year and not cause the GWB and GAWA to be recalculated does not accumulate. If the GWB falls below the GAWA at the end of a contract year, the GAWA will be reset to equal the GWB. This may occur, when over time, payment of guaranteed withdrawals is nearly complete and the GWB has been depleted.
data.benefitBaseOther: EFFECTIVE APRIL 27, 2020, THIS ADD-ON BENEFIT IS NO LONGER AVAILABLE ON TAX-QUALIFIED CONTRACTS.
data.notes: At the end of the GMWB Maturity Year, an amount equal to the excess of the GWB over contract value will be paid to the owner. If the GWB is less than the contract value, no payment will be made. In either case, the GWB will be set to zero and the GMWB will terminate. The GMWB maturity year is determined as per the schedule prescribed by the Issuer based on the owner's attained age on the latest required date for the first Stretch RMD. When determining the GMWB maturity year, the endorsement effective date is considered the beginning of the first contract year. The Stretch RMD is the amount defined by the IRS as the minimum distribution requirement under the life expectancy payout method applicable to the contract which is attributable to proceeds from the death of an owner of a qualified plan, or the death of an owner of a tax-qualified or non-qualified annuity contract. This GMWB is available if, the owner has already commenced receiving the required minimum distributions prior to the issue date of this GMWB, or if a trust was the designated beneficiary of the death benefit proceeds or owner must meet the applicable minimum distribution requirements by electing the life expectancy payout method or owner must commence the minimum distributions not later than 1 year after the deceased owner's death. This GMWB is only available for Beneficiary IRAs and non-qualified stretches. Owners age 70 or less may elect the benefit no more than five years after the death of the original owner; Owners age 71 through 80 on the GMWB effective date, may only elect the benefit if the Owner has not already begun taking distributions to meet the death payout requirements.
data.withdrawalNotes: This GMWB allows withdrawals greater than the GAWA to meet the contract's stretch RMD without compromising the endorsement's guarantees.
data.feeOption: Charges may increase by 0.2% annually on each 5th contract anniversary and the owner may elect to opt out of the current and future charges increases, upon such election, no future payments will be allowed.

data.name: LifeGuard Freedom Accelerator GMWB
data.availWhenAdded: No longer available for new purchases.
data.effectChangeOwnership: Ownership can be change, however designated life cannot be changed (original ownership).
data.gmwbCancellation: Once elected may not be cancelled.
data.gmwbTermination: Rider terminates on the earliest of 1) annuitization, 2) total withdrawal of contract value, 3) Death of the owner or 4) all obligations under the contract are satisfied.
data.spousalContinuationOption: Surviving spouse may elect to continue benefit after death of owner.
data.subsequentPremium: With each subsequent premium on the contract, the GWB and GAWA are recalculated. GWB increasing by the amount of premium net applicable taxes and GAWA equals the GAWA prior to the premium payment, plus the lesser of a) GAWA percentage multiplied by the subsequent premium payments or b) GAWA percentage multiplied by the increase in GWB.
data.partialWithdrawals: Withdrawals cause the GWB to be recalculated and also the GAWA, if withdrawal plus all the prior withdrawals in the contract year, exceeds the greater of the GAWA or RMD.
data.benefitDescription: Rider provides lifetime income protection with opportunities to grow the income through step-ups and deferral credit features.
data.benefitBaseGeneral: The Guaranteed Withdrawal Base (GWB) is equal to the initial premium net of any premium taxes. On each Contract Anniversary after issue, if the Contract Value is greater than the GWB, the GWB will be automatically reset to the Contract Value on that Contract Anniversary. GWB is used to calculate the Guaranteed Annual Withdrawal Amount (GAWA), which is equal to the withdrawal percentage multiplied by GWB.
data.benefitBaseNoWithdrawal: During the deferral credit period, if no partial withdrawals are taken, at the end of each contract anniversary, the GAWA percentage will be recalculated by adding Deferral Credit Percentage to it. Deferral Credit Percentage varies according to age and are determined on the designated life's age on the rider issue date. Deferral Credit Period begins on the rider effective date and ends on the earliest of - 1) rider is terminated, 2) 15th contract anniversary following the rider effective date, 3) contract anniversary immediately following the Designated Life's 90th birthday, 4) contract value falls to zero, or 5) Life Income option is elected.
data.benefitBaseWithdrawal: If GWB is less than the GAWA, at the end of any contract year, the GAWA will be set equal to the GWB. When withdrawals plus all prior withdrawals in the contract year is less than the GAWA or RMD, the GWB is recalculated, equaling the greater of the GWB before withdrawal, less withdrawals or zero and GAWA remains unchanged. When withdrawals plus all prior withdrawals in the contract year is exceeds the GAWA or RMD, GWB is recalculated, equaling greatest of the 1) the GWB prior to the withdrawal, first reduced dollar-for-dollar for withdrawals other than the excess withdrawals and then reduced proportionally to the contract value, in case of excess withdrawals, or 2) zero. GAWA is also recalculated as - GAWA prior to the withdrawal is reduced proportionally to the contract value, due to excess withdrawals.
data.benefitBaseEnhanceStep: On each contract anniversary, if the contract value is greater than the GWB, the GWB will automatically step-up to the contract value. If step-up occurs after the GAWA has been determined, the GAWA is recalculated, equaling the greater of - 1) GAWA percentage multiplied by the new GWB or 2) the GAWA prior to step-up.
data.notes: Cumulative premium payments are limited to the lesser of 5% of first-year premium payments or $10,000. After each payment when the contract value is zero, the GWB is recalculated equaling greater of 1) The GWB before payment less payment or 2) zero and GAWA remains unchanged.
data.withdrawalNotes: GAWA percentages varies according to age and are determined on the designated life's age on the rider issue date.
data.feeOption: On each 5th contract anniversary, the rider charge may increase. Maximum increase up to 0.24% could be made at a time. Also, it may increase due to future deferral credits, automatic step-ups or any other increase to GWB or GAWA.

data.benefitDescription: The rider provides a guaranteed annual lifetime withdrawal benefit, regardless of the market conditions. Rider also allows for different options to increase the Withdrawal Base used to determine the lifetime withdrawal amount under the rider - 1) bonus option; 2) step-up option; and 3) re-set opportunity.
data.benefitBaseGeneral: Guaranteed Withdrawal Base (GWB) is used to determine Guaranteed Annual Withdrawal Amount (GAWA) under the rider, by multiplying GWB value with the GAWA percentage. Initially, the GWB is equal to the initial premium net of any applicable premium taxes, if rider issued on contract issue; or if issued later, GWB will be equal to the contract value. On each Contract Anniversary after the rider issue, GWB increases with the elected bonus percentage from the available bonus range; and if the Contract Value is greater than the GWB, the GWB will be automatically reset to the Contract Value on that Contract Anniversary. On each contract anniversary, GWB is increased by Bonus Amount, equals to the Bonus Percentage 4% multiplied by Bonus Base, available at the earliest of 1) 10th contract anniversary; or 2) withdrawals are initiated under the rider. Initially the Bonus Base will be equal to the Contract Value, thereafter, is adjusted for withdrawals and any subsequent premium payments. If the withdrawals (including all prior withdrawals) in the current contract year, exceeds the greater of the GAWA and the RMD, then the Bonus Base is set to the lesser of the 1) GWB after the withdrawal; or 2) Bonus Base prior to withdrawals. Bonus Base may also increase by any step-up amount, if GWB is increased due to step-up, thereby, resets the Bonus Period of 10 years.
data.benefitBaseNoWithdrawal: Owner receives a GWB Adjustment, if no withdrawals are taken from the Contract on or before the later of 1) the Contract Anniversary on or immediately following the owner's 70th birthday; or 2) the 12th Contract Anniversary following the effective date of the rider. The GWB Adjustment is 105% of the GWB subject to the maximum of $10 million.
data.benefitBaseEnhanceStep: On each contract anniversary following the effective date of the rider, if Contract Value is greater than the GWB, the GWB will be automatically re-set to the Highest Quarterly Contract Value. The Highest Quarterly Contract Value is equal to the highest of the quarterly adjusted Contract Values from the four most recent Contract Quarterly Anniversaries, including the Contract Anniversary upon which the step-up is determined. The quarterly adjusted Contract Value is equal to the Contract Value on the Contract Quarterly Anniversary, plus any Premium paid subsequent to that Contract Quarterly Anniversary, net of any applicable Premium taxes, and adjusted for any partial withdrawals taken subsequent to that Contract Quarterly Anniversary.
data.withdrawalNotes: GAWA percentage is determined at the time of first withdrawal, varying according to the designated life's attained age and the Income Stream Level selected.
data.initialResetText: If no withdrawals are made and GWB adjustment is available, GWB is re-set to the greater of the 1) current GWB; or 2) GWB Adjustment. No adjustments are made to the Bonus Base.
data.feeOption: On each fifth Contract Anniversary, the charge may be increased. Owner may elect to opt-out of the charge increase, however then all future increase to GWB and GAWA% will be forfeited.

Rider also allows for different options to increase the Withdrawal Base used to determine the lifetime withdrawal amount under the rider - 1) bonus percentage; 2) step-up options; 3) re-set opportunity; and 4) option to elect death benefit.
data.benefitBaseGeneral: Guaranteed Withdrawal Base (GWB) is used to determine Guaranteed Annual Withdrawal Amount (GAWA) under the rider, by multiplying GWB value with the GAWA percentage. Initially, the GWB is equal to the initial premium net of any applicable premium taxes, if rider issued on contract issue; or if issued later, GWB will be equal to the contract value. On each Contract Anniversary after the rider issue, GWB increases with the elected bonus percentage from the available bonus range; and if the Contract Value is greater than the GWB, the GWB will be automatically reset to the Contract Value on that Contract Anniversary. On each contract anniversary, GWB is increased by Bonus Amount, equals to the Bonus Percentage 6% multiplied by Bonus Base, available at the earliest of 1) 10th contract anniversary; or 2) withdrawals are initiated under the rider. Initially the Bonus Base will be equal to the Contract Value, thereafter, is adjusted for withdrawals and any subsequent premium payments. If the withdrawals (including all prior withdrawals) in the current contract year, exceeds the greater of the GAWA and the RMD, then the Bonus Base is set to the lesser of the 1) GWB after the withdrawal; or 2) Bonus Base prior to withdrawals. Bonus Base may also increase by any step-up amount, if GWB is increased due to step-up, thereby, resets the Bonus Period of 10 years.
data.benefitBaseNoWithdrawal: Owner receives a GWB Adjustment, if no withdrawals are taken from the Contract on or before the later of 1) the Contract Anniversary on or immediately following the owner's 70th birthday; or 2) the 12th Contract Anniversary following the effective date of the rider. The GWB Adjustment is 105% of the GWB subject to the maximum of $10 million.
data.benefitBaseEnhanceStep: On each contract anniversary following the effective date of the rider, if Contract Value is greater than the GWB, the GWB will be automatically re-set to the Highest Quarterly Contract Value. The Highest Quarterly Contract Value is equal to the highest of the quarterly adjusted Contract Values from the four most recent Contract Quarterly Anniversaries, including the Contract Anniversary upon which the step-up is determined. The quarterly adjusted Contract Value is equal to the Contract Value on the Contract Quarterly Anniversary, plus any Premium paid subsequent to that Contract Quarterly Anniversary, net of any applicable Premium taxes, and adjusted for any partial withdrawals taken subsequent to that Contract Quarterly Anniversary.

data.benefitDescription: The rider provides a guaranteed annual lifetime withdrawal benefit and allows the Owner to add a portion of earnings to the otherwise permissible withdrawals. The For Life Guarantee becomes effective on the Contract Anniversary immediately following the Owner (or oldest Owner) attaining age 59 1/2.
data.benefitBaseGeneral: The initial Guaranteed Withdrawal Base (GWB) is equal to the initial purchase payment. On each Contract Anniversary after issue, if the Contract Value is greater than the GWB, the GWB will be automatically reset to the Contract Value on that Contract Anniversary. A 4% bonus will apply to the benefit base in years no withdrawals are taken, if greater than the stepped up value. Step-Up also allows for a potential increase in the GAWA percentage in the event that the Step-Up occurs after the first withdrawal. Whether there will be any such increase in the GAWA percentage will depend on a value called the Benefit Determination Baseline (BDB). The initial BDB equals the initial premium, net of applicable premium taxes. Upon Step-Up, if the GWB is greater than the BDB and an age band is crossed, the GAWA percentage will be re-determined based on the attained age of the Owner. Benefit also provides Earnings-Sensitive Adjustment, which is an amount that can be withdrawn each Contract Year when there are benefit earnings, in addition to GAWA while keeping the rider guarantees fully in effect. The adjustment is equal to the lesser of (1) 40% of benefit earnings, 2) 2/3 of the greater of remaining (a) GAWA (b) RMD. If there are no earnings in the benefit, no earnings sensitive adjustment will be applied.
data.benefitBaseNoWithdrawal: A bonus of 4% for single life and joint life of the Bonus Base will be added to the GWB at the end of each Contract Year within the Bonus Period if no withdrawals have been taken during that Contract Year. The Bonus Base at issue is equal to the GWB. It increases dollar for dollar with subsequent net premiums. If withdrawals in a Contract Year exceed the GAWA plus ESA, the Bonus Base is reset to the lesser of the GWB after the withdrawal and the Bonus Base before the withdrawal. If withdrawals in a contract year do not exceed the GAWA plus ESA no adjustment is made to the bonus base. When the GWB increases on a Step-Up, the Bonus Base is set to the greater of the GWB after, and the Bonus Base before, the Step-Up. The bonus period begins on the effective date of the benefit and is reset at the time of a step-up of the bonus base if the step-up occurs on or before the contract anniversary immediately following the owners ( or older joint owners) 80th Birthday. The Bonus Period ends on the earliest of (1) the 10th Contract Anniversary after rider issue or most recent step up or (3) contract value reduced to zero. It is possible for the Bonus Period to expire and then re-start.
data.benefitBaseEnhanceStep: If no withdrawals are taken before the later of: (1) the Contract Anniversary on or immediately following the 70th birthday or (2) the 12th Contract Anniversary, the GWB will be reset on that date to the greater of the GWB Adjustment or the current GWB. The GWB Adjustment is equal to (1) the 105% of net premiums received in the first Contract Year, plus (3) net premiums received after the first Contract Year.
data.withdrawalNotes: Automatic step-ups after first withdrawal may increase the GAWA percentage.
data.chargeNotes: Charges may increase subject to maximum on each 5th contract anniversary and the owner may elect to opt out of the current and future charges increases.

vaCharges.maintainanceFeesWaiver: Waived if contract value is or exceeds $50,000 on assessment date.
vaCharges.notes: Issuer imposes $22.50 as an expedited delivery charge for overnight delivery on Saturday; otherwise, the overnight delivery charge is $10 for withdrawals. Charge for wire transfers in connection with withdrawals is $25 for International wire and $20 for Standard wire. Advisory fees are capped at an annual rate of 1.50% of the Contract Value and cannot exceed this rate if no optional benefit is elected.

data.notes: Owner may withdraw a specified dollar amount (of at least $50 per withdrawal) or a specified percentage or earnings periodically. Issuer, reserved the right to defer payment for a withdrawal or transfer from the Fixed Account for up to six months or the period permitted by law.

vaSchdTransAssetRebalancings.notes: Automatically relocate your Contract Value among Investment Divisions and the one-year Fixed Account Option to maintain your chosen allocation percentages automatically.
vaSchdTransAssetRebalancings.assetRebalCancellation: May be canceled any time after the election.
vaSchdTransAssetRebalancings.assetRebalTermination: May be terminated any time after the election.

vaSchdTransDollarCostAverages.notes: Transfers available from any Investment Divisions into any Investment Divisions and Fixed Account Option through the Dollar Cost Averaging (DCA) program.
vaSchdTransDollarCostAverages.dcaCancellation: May be cancelled any time after election.
vaSchdTransDollarCostAverages.dcaTermination: May be terminated any time after election.

vaSchdTransDollarCostAverages.notes: Issuer will offer special enhanced interest rates on the DCA+ Fixed Account Option. If a DCA+ Fixed Account Option is selected, monies in the DCA+ Fixed Account Option will be systematically transferred to the Investment Divisions or other Fixed Account Options chosen over a DCA+ term of either twelve months or six months, as owner select.
vaSchdTransDollarCostAverages.dcaCancellation: May be cancelled any time after election.
vaSchdTransDollarCostAverages.dcaTermination: May be terminated any time after election.

vaSchdTransEarningSweeps.notes: May only be added within 30 days of the contract issue date. Transfers can be made from the one-year Fixed Account Option, if currently available, and the JNL/Dreyfus Government Money Market into other Investment Divisions and Fixed Account Options.
vaSchdTransEarningSweeps.optTermination: May be terminated any time after election.
vaSchdTransEarningSweeps.optCancellation: May be cancelled any time after election.

data.notes: Issuer reserves right to pay annuity payment in lump sum, if it is less than $2,000 and right to change frequency of payments, if it is less than $20 to the frequency where at least $20 will be paid. Owner may choose to have income payments made monthly, quarterly, semi-annually or annually. Life Annuity with 10 Years Guaranteed Period is a default annuity option.
